# Deploying inkling with GPUStack and vLLM

This tutorial guides you through setting up **inkling**—the official unquantized/FP16 Mixture-of-Experts model with massive long-context capabilities—using **vLLM (nightly)** in the **GPUStack** Custom Container mode. 

---

## 🛠️ Prerequisites & Setup

### 1. Base Image
* **Image Name**: `vllm/vllm-openai:nightly`
* **Hardware Requirements**: H20*2

### 2. Model Weights Source
* **Model Name**: `inkling`
* **Download Source (ModelScope)**: `https://modelscope.cn/models/thinkingmachines/Inkling`

---

## 🚀 GPUStack Configuration Steps

Navigate to your GPUStack admin dashboard, go to Models -> deployment, and select the model deploy / modelscope mode.

### 1. Basic Information
* **Model Name**: `inkling`
* **Container Image**: `vllm/vllm-openai:nightly`

### 2. Backend Arguments 
You can directly copy and paste the following parameters into the **server Arguments** text area in GPUStack (each argument occupies a single line without backslashes):

TDEP
* $node0-ip should be replace with your node 0 ip address

node 0
```text
--trust-remote-code
--tokenizer-mode=inkling
--kernel-config.enable_flashinfer_autotune=False
--tensor-parallel-size=8
--data-parallel-size=2
--data-parallel-size-local=1
--enable-expert-parallel
--data-parallel-rpc-port=13389
--data-parallel-address=$node0-ip
--data-parallel-hybrid-lb
--max-model-len=131072
--max-num-seqs=10
--enable-auto-tool-choice
--tool-call-parser=inkling
--speculative-config '{"method":"mtp","num_speculative_tokens":1}'
--reasoning-parser=inkling
```

node 1
```text
--trust-remote-code
--tokenizer-mode=inkling
--kernel-config.enable_flashinfer_autotune=False
--tensor-parallel-size=8
--data-parallel-size=2
--data-parallel-size-local=1
--data-parallel-start-rank 1
--enable-expert-parallel
--data-parallel-rpc-port=13389
--data-parallel-address=$node0-ip
--data-parallel-hybrid-lb
--max-model-len=131072
--max-num-seqs=10
--enable-auto-tool-choice
--tool-call-parser=inkling
--speculative-config '{"method":"mtp","num_speculative_tokens":1}'
--reasoning-parser=inkling
```

